      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 5.1</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 5.1</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>天地不仁，以萬物為芻狗；</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Heaven and earth do not act from (the impulse of) any wish to be benevolent; they deal with all things as the dogs of grass are dealt with. The sages do not act from (any wish to be) benevolent; they deal with the people as the dogs of grass are dealt with. May not the space between heaven and earth be compared to a bellows?</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
